    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-01-02T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-01-02T07:00:00-05:00" n="162"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d162">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">741.61/916: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-01-02T15:00:00+03:00"
                            >January 2, 1941—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 2—12:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5. The British Ambassador<note n="95" xml:id="d162fn95">Sir Stafford
                        Cripps.</note> told me this morning that he has continued to maintain his
                    attitude of aloofness towards the Soviet Government and that he has not seen any
                    of the higher officials of the Commissariat for Foreign Affairs since November
                    19.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
